data.title: September 2013 – Saint Elizabeth Roman Catholic Church
data.text:
Introduction Elizabeth of Hungary was born on July 7, 1207, in the Kingdom of Hungary. She was a princess, the daughter of King Andrew II of Hungary and Gertrude of Merania. She was a greatly venerated Catholic. She died on November 17, 1231 at the age of 24. Early Life and Marriage St. Elizabeth was…

Dear Friends, St. Elizabeth’s Basic School is a Roman Catholic Early Childhood Learning Centre that nurtures and encourages children between the ages of three years old and five years old.
